│ already been correctly determined by `getInsertPointForBundle`.\n\n4. **Proposed Edit      │
│ Point(s)**: The fix is to remove the incorrect call to `setInsertPointAfterBundle` from    │
│ `BoUpSLP::createBuildVector`. The insertion point is already correctly set by the          │
│ `Builder.SetInsertPoint(InsertPoint)` call just before it.\n\nFile:                        │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`\nLines: 16475-16475\n\n```cpp\n-         │
│ setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);\n```\n\n5. **Conclusion**: The crash is caused by an         │
│ incorrect call to `setInsertPointAfterBundle` within `createBuildVector` when preparing to │
│ build a vector from the scalar operands of a PHI node bundle. This function incorrectly    │
│ assumes it is operating on a PHI bundle itself. Removing this erroneous call resolves the  │
│ assertion failure by preventing `getLastInstructionInBundle` from being called on a        │
│ non-PHI `TreeEntry`. The insertion point for the new `build_vector` is already correctly   │
│ established by `getInsertPointForBundle`, so removing the line does not cause any other    │
│ issues."                                                                                   │
│ }                                                                                          │
